Your Points Expire Today

I was telling Mike about that trail you mentioned last week. We finally had a chance to scout it out on Saturday. The weather was perfect, overcast but no rain, which made the climb really comfortable. We packed way too much food as usual but the sandwiches hit different at the summit. Let me know if you want the GPX file.

There's this little diner about 10 miles from the trailhead that does a fantastic breakfast burrito. Might be worth tacking on to the next trip. Also, I finally replaced those worn-out boots I had been complaining about. Broke them in on the descent and they felt great. Hoping to get out again next month if schedules align.

