Thank you for being a valued Walmart member.

So I finally picked up that sci-fi novel you recommended. I have to say, the first hundred pages were a bit of a slog because of the world-building density but once the main plot kicked in around chapter 12 I couldn't put it down. The author's take on AI ethics was surprisingly nuanced for a page-turner. Have you read the sequel yet? I heard it focuses on a different character entirely which sounds risky but maybe it works.

Also, I saw that the streaming adaptation has been greenlit with a really interesting director attached. Not sure how they'll handle the nonlinear timeline without confusing the average viewer but I'm cautiously optimistic. Let me know if you want to borrow the hardcover copy I have.

